used to talk about shooting that light out that was

14:39.760 --> 14:46.368
on top of the academic building. And he said that 
when he was a student, they called it Prexy's Moon.

14:54.297 --> 14:55.599
And that they would shoot at it.

14:59.604 --> 15:00.144
Let's see. I forgot to ask about Jack Williams, 
President Williams. You worked with him. What was

15:08.159 --> 15:10.342
your evaluation of him?

15:13.165 --> 15:26.562
I've always thought that nobody but Earl Rudder 
could have done what he did and nobody but Jack

15:13.165 --> 15:26.562
Williams could have done what he did immediately 
after. That it was the two of them. Do you agree with

15:28.644 --> 15:31.188
that? The two of them did what needed to be done and 
laid the foundation for A&M as it is today.

15:44.089 --> 15:48.877
What do you remember most about Dr. Williams?

15:58.271 --> 15:58.972
Very likable.

16:02.378 --> 16:03.900
I remember a good sense of humor.

16:09.871 --> 16:11.853
I worked very closely with Dr. Williams. And then 
with Mr. Rudder, I was the secretary of the

16:13.796 --> 16:28.854
Aspirations Committee and wrote that report for 
the faculty that recommended women, volunteer

16:13.796 --> 16:28.854
corps, racial integration, and higher admission 
requirements. Damn it. Pretty good. Yes. Let's

16:34.601 --> 16:35.963
see.

16:41.123 --> 16:42.586
Well, then I'm about through. The last question I 
wanted to ask, what feelings do you have in your

16:42.646 --> 16:50.703
heart today about A&M? Very close to A&M. Yes, sir.

16:57.817 --> 17:00.102
I give it all my money. I get pretty good.

